RACE.RACE_TEXT: LOUISIANA DOWNS RACE 1 6 1/2F Dirt CR: 54. Maiden Claiming Purse 11000. FOR MAIDENS, THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 119 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Claiming Price $7,500 Accredited Arkansas, Louisiana, and Texas Bred Preferred.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: RED RAIDER XPRESS was off a step slow but was given time to find his stride, started to gain ground at the seven sixteenth pole, angled out five wide to find clear racing room, circled the field through the turn, was five wide in the stretch and had clear racing room, was put to task and driven after the quarter pole, was encouraged and driven and closed with a vengeance, which paid off with the honors of the win. UNAFFILIATED hopped at the start, settled in along the fence and started to slowly gain ground and momentum, improved position by the three eighths pole, saved ground and passed up the rail, closed at the sixteenth pole and was up in time for second. OLD TOBY vied for the early lead, ended up matching strides with another rival while setting the pace, gave way in mid stretch. LAKE HAMILTON raced along the rail while stalking the pace early, was given the cue and angled out at the three eighths pole, gained ground and was in contention in the stretch but had no late kick. OCEAN KISS vied for the early lead, matched strides with an inside rival as this set managed the pace, was in contention in the stretch but tired in the lane. RAY'S BIG BOY showed little early on and was pulled up in the stretch. RAY'S BIG BOY WAS VANNED OFF.

ENTRY.COMMENT: vied, matched strides, co-led, rail trip, tired late.

NATE'S ATTACK raced mid pack in the four path on a loose rein, fanned out six wide at the quarter pole, challenged for the lead and battled with another rival through the stretch but just missed. RACE.RACE_TEXT: LOUISIANA DOWNS RACE 3 1M 70Y Dirt CR: 59. Claiming Purse 16250. FOR ACCREDITED LA BRED FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON THREE RACES. Three Year Olds, 119 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race At A Mile Or Over Since April 15, 2023 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $7,500.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: REALITOS took advantage of the one post position and took the lead while staying on the fence, was stalked by on outside rival for the first have of the race, was threatened by this rival for the lead at the five sixteenth pole, responded well to the challenge and battled back while not giving up any ground, the set drew away from the rest of the field as they battled for the win, REALITOS was kept to task and kept trying and was able to take the win. FUHR MEO stalked the pace setter from the three path, launched a bid and challenged for the lead at the five sixteenth pole, matched strides and battled for the lead, drew away from the rest of the field, but could not get past REALITOS and had to settle for the place honors. TRINITY HOPE was racing mid pack in the four path, was cued at the three eighths, gained some ground but did not have enough today to threaten the set that was in front of him. STAR'S DREAM raced along the rail and was able to save ground, launched a mild bid but to no avail. I DONT KNOW EITHER was off a step slow, tucked in behind horses and saved ground early, patiently rated behind horses until the have mile marker, edged out into the five path and launched a bid, was encouraged, driven, after the quarter pole, drifted out in the lane and faded. ZEEROCK raced 3w and was never involved. GIFTED TALENT raced two wide and trailed through out.
